OL,3,CPensioner devastated after losing
OL,4,C#20,000 life savings in banking scam
OL,6,F"Usually the scammers ask for your
OL,7,Fcard details don't they, so straight
OL,8,Faway I thought it must be Lloyds, it
OL,9,Fmust be a genuine call."
OL,11,FBut it wasn't - during the
OL,12,Fconversation they told him someone was
OL,13,Ftrying to access his account and
OL,14,Fconvinced him that someone at the
OL,15,Flocal branch was working with
OL,16,Ffraudsters.
OL,18,FHe says they asked him to move his
OL,19,Fmoney to a secure account and not to
OL,20,Fsay anything to the staff.
