OL,6,F"If you're ever in doubt, hang up and
OL,7,Fcall back on a number you trust, not
OL,8,Fone you've been given over the phone.
OL,9,FDon't be rushed into anything, and if
OL,10,Fa message is claiming to be from
OL,11,Fsomeone you know, contact them in a
OL,12,Fdifferent way, to confirm it is them."
OL,14,FLeonard is trying to move on from
OL,15,Fwhat's happened and hopes by sharing
OL,16,Fhis story he can help others not make
OL,17,Fthe same mistake he did.
